dct_description_sm: O. H. Tittmann, Superintendent ; Original surveys 1870 to 1910 ; Harbor surveys from U.S. Engineers to 1911 and other sources.
Contour and spot-height relief with depths shown by soundings and shading (at low-water areas).
Buoy legend, Point Fermin coordinates and statistics, table of abbreviations (for seabed makeup), tidal information.
3 bar scales in statute miles, nautical miles, and kilometers.
City plans, streets, railroads, coastal topography (rocks, seawead, low-water, etc.), marshland, lights.
